President Biden held a meeting with labor and business leaders to discuss the infrastructure bill. He emphasized the importance of bipartisan support for the bill and the need for the United States to make fundamental changes to generate growth. The President highlighted the race for the future and the need to connect all Americans to high-speed internet, repair infrastructure, electrify school buses and transit systems, build charging networks for electric vehicles, and update the power grid. He emphasized the need to win the competition for the 21st century. The President also briefly addressed the COVID-19 pandemic, stating that vaccinated individuals are safe and have a low chance of getting infected or experiencing severe symptoms. The administration is closely monitoring the situation and following the guidance of public health officials.